[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":401},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-18-next-structure\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-18-next-structure\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-18-next-structure\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-18-next-structure\u002F":378,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F01\u002Flearn-hexo-18-next-structure\u002F":387},"\u002Fhexo\u002F20201001\u002F1805633629\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":361,"date":362,"description":19,"extension":363,"lang":364,"meta":365,"navigation":251,"path":366,"readingMinutes":367,"seo":368,"standalone":369,"stem":370,"tags":371,"tldr":375,"updated":362,"url":376,"__hash__":377},"content\u002Fen\u002FHexo\u002Flearn-hexo-18-next-structure.md","(18) Learning Hexo from Scratch - NexT Theme: Understanding the NexT Structure","9263365081",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":352},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,64,78,81,88,95,103,105,111,113,118,120,123,131,134,156,162,166,169,172,178,181,311,314,317,334,348],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This post is a quick tour of the NexT folder structure.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"next-folder-layout","NexT folder layout",[25,26,27,34,39,44,49,54,59],"ul",{},[28,29,30],"li",{},[31,32,33],"code",{},"docs",[28,35,36],{},[31,37,38],{},"languages",[28,40,41],{},[31,42,43],{},"layout",[28,45,46],{},[31,47,48],{},"scripts",[28,50,51],{},[31,52,53],{},"source",[28,55,56],{},[31,57,58],{},"_config.yml",[28,60,61],{},[31,62,63],{},"gulpfile.js",[17,65,66,67,70,71,70,74,77],{},"Other files I didn't list aren't worth worrying about — you basically never touch them. Things like ",[31,68,69],{},".eslintrc.json",", ",[31,72,73],{},".travis.yml",[31,75,76],{},".editorconfig",", etc. — these only matter if you're developing a theme yourself.",[17,79,80],{},"You might be thinking: \"Wait, even with the NexT theme I have to change things? I just learned all this and it's still not enough?!\"",[17,82,83],{},[84,85],"img",{"alt":86,"src":87},"No mercy!","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F2deb2e2395fa48338fb817415c3df952.jpg",[17,89,90,91,94],{},"Unless you're planning customisations, you basically don't have to touch anything — most config edits will be in ",[31,92,93],{},"themes\u002F_config.yml",".",[17,96,97,98,102],{},"But ",[99,100,101],"del",{},"to pad out the Ironman post count"," in case some folks want to customise, it's worth getting familiar with the structure.",[12,104,33],{"id":33},[17,106,107,108,110],{},"The ",[31,109,33],{}," folder is what it sounds like — documentation. Currently three languages: English, Simplified Chinese, and Russian.",[12,112,38],{"id":38},[17,114,115,117],{},[31,116,38],{}," contains the language packs for various locales — about 22 of them.",[12,119,43],{"id":43},[17,121,122],{},"NexT uses the swig templating engine. If you've written EJS, swig will feel familiar — they're really similar. If you're in VSCode, there's a swig extension that adds file recognition:",[17,124,125],{},[126,127,128],"a",{"href":128,"rel":129},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=zhutian.swig",[130],"nofollow",[17,132,133],{},"The folder breaks down into:",[25,135,136,141,146,151],{},[28,137,138],{},[31,139,140],{},"_macro",[28,142,143],{},[31,144,145],{},"_partials",[28,147,148],{},[31,149,150],{},"_scripts",[28,152,153],{},[31,154,155],{},"_third-party",[17,157,158,159,161],{},"The one you'll usually focus on is ",[31,160,145],{}," — most feature additions involve editing swig files in here.",[12,163,165],{"id":164},"scripts-source","scripts & source",[17,167,168],{},"These two folders hold CSS and JavaScript, including third-party plugins. NexT uses stylus as its CSS preprocessor.",[17,170,171],{},"You can install language-stylus for syntax highlighting and file recognition:",[17,173,174],{},[126,175,176],{"href":176,"rel":177},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=sysoev.language-stylus",[130],[17,179,180],{},"If you've got a Sass or SCSS background, this'll look familiar:",[182,183,188],"pre",{"className":184,"code":185,"language":186,"meta":187,"style":187},"language-styl shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast",".header-inner {\n  background: var(--content-bg-color);\n  border-radius: $border-radius-inner;\n  box-shadow: $box-shadow-inner;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  padding: 0;\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 0;\n  width: $sidebar-desktop;\n\n  +desktop-large() {\n    width: $sidebar-desktop;\n  }\n\n  +tablet-mobile() {\n    border-radius: initial;\n    position: relative;\n    width: auto;\n  }\n}\n","styl","",[31,189,190,198,204,210,216,222,228,234,240,246,253,259,265,271,276,282,288,294,300,305],{"__ignoreMap":187},[191,192,195],"span",{"class":193,"line":194},"line",1,[191,196,197],{},".header-inner {\n",[191,199,201],{"class":193,"line":200},2,[191,202,203],{},"  background: var(--content-bg-color);\n",[191,205,207],{"class":193,"line":206},3,[191,208,209],{},"  border-radius: $border-radius-inner;\n",[191,211,213],{"class":193,"line":212},4,[191,214,215],{},"  box-shadow: $box-shadow-inner;\n",[191,217,219],{"class":193,"line":218},5,[191,220,221],{},"  overflow: hidden;\n",[191,223,225],{"class":193,"line":224},6,[191,226,227],{},"  padding: 0;\n",[191,229,231],{"class":193,"line":230},7,[191,232,233],{},"  position: absolute;\n",[191,235,237],{"class":193,"line":236},8,[191,238,239],{},"  top: 0;\n",[191,241,243],{"class":193,"line":242},9,[191,244,245],{},"  width: $sidebar-desktop;\n",[191,247,249],{"class":193,"line":248},10,[191,250,252],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":251},true,"\n",[191,254,256],{"class":193,"line":255},11,[191,257,258],{},"  +desktop-large() {\n",[191,260,262],{"class":193,"line":261},12,[191,263,264],{},"    width: $sidebar-desktop;\n",[191,266,268],{"class":193,"line":267},13,[191,269,270],{},"  }\n",[191,272,274],{"class":193,"line":273},14,[191,275,252],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":251},[191,277,279],{"class":193,"line":278},15,[191,280,281],{},"  +tablet-mobile() {\n",[191,283,285],{"class":193,"line":284},16,[191,286,287],{},"    border-radius: initial;\n",[191,289,291],{"class":193,"line":290},17,[191,292,293],{},"    position: relative;\n",[191,295,297],{"class":193,"line":296},18,[191,298,299],{},"    width: auto;\n",[191,301,303],{"class":193,"line":302},19,[191,304,270],{},[191,306,308],{"class":193,"line":307},20,[191,309,310],{},"}\n",[12,312,63],{"id":313},"gulpfilejs",[17,315,316],{},"I've never actually opened this file. NexT doesn't use it during normal usage. Quick skim suggests it's for testing, so you can ignore it.",[17,318,319,320,323,324,327,328,331,332,94],{},"If you're curious, you can ",[31,321,322],{},"cd themes\u002Fnext",", install packages with ",[31,325,326],{},"npm install",", and run ",[31,329,330],{},"npm run test",". You'll probably hit some errors related to third-party packages, so you can ignore ",[31,333,63],{},[17,335,336,337,340,341,343,344,347],{},"One heads up — if you do ",[31,338,339],{},"cd"," into that folder and run ",[31,342,326],{},", remember to delete the ",[31,345,346],{},"node_modules"," afterwards.",[349,350,351],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":187,"searchDepth":200,"depth":200,"links":353},[354,355,356,357,358,359,360],{"id":14,"depth":200,"t